Sentencas: A Ru-free anode was developed for the direct utilization of iso-octane in low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: An octane-fueled low temperature solid oxide fuel cell with Ru-free anodes

Sentencas: The anode was consisted of a Ni framework and a nano-sized oxygen-ion conductor, samaria-doped ceria (SI)C), which was coated onto the inner surface of the framework via an ion impregnation process.
Titulo: An octane-fueled low temperature solid oxide fuel cell with Ru-free anodes

Sentencas: Compared with the cells based on conventional Ni-SDC anodes, single cells with the SDC-coated Ni anodes exhibited improved stability and enhanced electrochemical activity.
Titulo: An octane-fueled low temperature solid oxide fuel cell with Ru-free anodes

Sentencas: Peak power density of similar to 400 MW cm(-2) was achieved at 600 degrees C, and power generation was relatively stable over 260 h when iso-octane-air mixture was directly used as the fuel.
Titulo: An octane-fueled low temperature solid oxide fuel cell with Ru-free anodes

Sentencas: The performance is comparable with those obtained using ceria-Ru as an internal reforming catalyst.
Titulo: An octane-fueled low temperature solid oxide fuel cell with Ru-free anodes
